cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision, specifically edge detection using convolutional neural networks. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of backpropagation for training, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a new method for edge detection, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions the use of convolutional features for image segmentation, which could place it in the cs.MM (Multimedia) category.
